A stealth startup is&nbsp;a new company that keeps its products, services, and operations secret until it's ready to launch.&nbsp;Stealth startups use this strategy to develop their ideas without the pressure of competitors, the media, or potential customers.&nbsp;

Why do startups go stealth?

Protect intellectual property

Stealth startups can keep their ideas secret to prevent competitors from stealing them&nbsp;

Avoid market disruption

Stealth startups can refine their products and services before launching to avoid disrupting the market&nbsp;

Manage public image

Stealth startups can use stealth mode as part of a marketing strategy to generate interest from potential customers&nbsp;

